Abortion should be available in the case of rape or incest, to save the life of the woman or from a risk of physical and/or mental harm.

The Health Services Executive (HSE) of Ireland, announced that a short-acting, orally consumed, drug will be made available as a safe option for medical abortion medical abortion. This medication can either be self-administered or administered in the company of a trained woman who is a nurse or midwife.

The Centre for Reproductive Rights and Women on Web, partnered together to bring clinic-like services to remote or rural areas, through website “treatment courses”, as an alternative to abortion.

Progress of the world's women 2015-2016: Transforming Economies, Realizing Rights, examines the role of international development cooperation in the achievement of women’s economic and social rights in development cooperation policies and programming. Drawing from over 430 accounts of national programs from governments, the UN, NGOs, and others, the international community has the tools to realize women’s rights, but there is still significant room for improvement.
